snippet.textDisplay:
Is there an English word for "VAK"?
"Vak" is a Swedish word, meaning "area of ice weaker than surrounding areas".
Caused by currents, vegetation or rocks, it can be hard to spot a vak just by looking at the ice.
Which is how people fall through the ice.
